1. Permission & Use

You are free to:

Use this work for personal, academic, experimental, or commercial purposes.

Modify it and create derivative works.

Distribute original or modified versions.

Incorporate it into larger systems, products, or mission architectures.

There are no restrictions on field of use (aerospace, defense, research, commercial, educational, etc.).

2. Attribution Requirement

Any reuse, distribution, or derivative work must:

Include clear attribution to Nathan Rudloff (creator) and

Reference the license name “Kaizen AI Integration License”.

Attribution must be visible in:

documentation,

README files,

or equivalent public-facing materials.

3. Commercial Use & Royalty Window

Commercial use is permitted under the following rule:

If a product or service incorporating this work generates >$100,000 USD in revenue in any 12-month period, a 3% royalty on revenue above that threshold is required.

Below that threshold, no royalty is owed.

Royalty payments must be arranged directly with the creator.
This royalty rule is intentionally simple to avoid corporate legal overhead.

